page.title: 11Insect life on the Marshes
page.content: When we visited the marshes we were fortunate enough to see several Blue Damsel flies that flitted around like large butterflies. Some of our friends have also spotted Tortoise shell, Peacock and Red Admiral butterflies as well as the large green dragonfly. We found the attractive catapillar of the Yellow_tail moth and also two species of snails, one of which we think was a White or Sandhill snail. The other snail seemed to be nocturnal, we could not encourage it out during the day but each morning there was the evidence left of its long silvery trail.
